# Core Library Package (indexed-core)

## Overview

The core library is the foundation of the Indexed system, providing document indexing, vector storage, and semantic search capabilities. It's designed to be used by the CLI and any future applications (server, API, etc.).

**Location:** `packages/indexed-core/`  
**Import Name:** `index` (from `indexed_core.src.index`)

## Current State: Dual Architecture

### Legacy Implementation (`index/legacy/`)

**Status:** Fully functional, battle-tested  
**Usage:** Currently used by CLI commands

**Structure:**
```
index/legacy/
├── core/                   # Document processing
├── services/              # Collection and search services
│   ├── collection_service.py
│   ├── search_service.py
│   ├── inspect_service.py
│   └── models.py
├── sources/               # Data source connectors
│   ├── jira/             # Jira Cloud/Server integration
│   ├── confluence/       # Confluence integration
│   └── files/            # Local file reading
├── indexes/               # Vector indexing
│   ├── indexers/         # FAISS indexer implementations
│   └── embeddings/       # Sentence transformer embeddings
├── persisters/            # Storage persistence
├── factories/             # Factory pattern implementations
└── utils/                 # Utility functions
```

**Characteristics:**
- Complex factory/adapter pattern
- Works well but hard to test
- Tight coupling between components
- Will be gradually migrated away from

